---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Action Sports Safety Project"
  description="How Action Sports Safety Project collects, uses, and protects information from website visitors and donors."
>
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content">
    <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="privacy-title">
      <div class="page-hero-inner">
        <div>
          <p class="page-hero-eyebrow" aria-hidden="true">Legal</p>
          <h1 class="page-hero-title" id="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="page-hero-lede">
          We collect very little. We do not sell or rent personal information. This
          working draft will be replaced by a counsel-reviewed version before launch.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-section">
      <div class="page-section-inner">
        <p class="prose-meta">
          <span>Effective date: To be set</span>
          <span>Last updated: Draft</span>
        </p>

        <div class="prose">
          <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
          <p>
            From visitors to this site, we collect basic, non-identifying analytics such
            as page views and approximate location at the country and city level. We do
            not use third-party advertising trackers.
          </p>
          <p>
            From donors, we collect the information needed to process and acknowledge a
            gift: name, email, mailing address, and the donation amount. Payment details
            are handled by a third-party payment processor and never stored on our
            servers.
          </p>
          <p>
            From grant applicants, we collect the information you submit on the
            application: name, location, contact, course details, and the financial-need
            statement. Financial-need information is kept confidential to the Grant
            Review Board.
          </p>

          <h2>2. How we use it</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>To process and acknowledge donations.</li>
            <li>To review and award grants.</li>
            <li>To send occasional updates if you opt in.</li>
            <li>To meet legal and tax reporting obligations.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. How we share it</h2>
          <p>
            We do not sell or rent personal information. We share data only with:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Service providers who help us operate (payment processor, email host).</li>
            <li>Tax authorities when required.</li>
            <li>Anyone you explicitly direct us to.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            This site uses minimal cookies, primarily for analytics. You can disable
            cookies in your browser; the site will continue to function.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            California residents have rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act
            (CCPA), including the right to know what we have collected and to request
            deletion. EU and UK residents have similar rights under GDPR. To exercise
            these rights, write
            <a href="mailto:privacy@actionsportssafetyproject.com">privacy@actionsportssafetyproject.com</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Children</h2>
          <p>
            This site is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
            information from children. If you believe we have, contact us and we will
            delete it.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Security</h2>
          <p>
            We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect personal
            information. No system is perfectly secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute
            security.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Changes</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this policy. Material changes will be reflected in the effective
            date above and announced where reasonable.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about privacy:
            <a href="mailto:privacy@actionsportssafetyproject.com">privacy@actionsportssafetyproject.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>
